196.7	Long-Term_Capital_Management	Long-Term Capital Management	Long-Term Capital Management L.P. was a speculative hedge fund based in Greenwich, Connecticut that utilized absolute-return trading strategies (such as fixed-income arbitrage, statistical arbitrage, and pairs trading) combined with high leverage. The firm's master hedge fund, Long-Term Capital Portfolio L.P., failed in the late 1990s, leading to a bailout by other financial institutions, under the supervision of the Federal Reserve.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/2/2c/Ltcm.png/220px-Ltcm.png
